  "texts": [
    "In particular, if m = 1, then Df (x) ∈ (R n) *.For a differential k-form ω, we denote its exterior derivative by dω.",
    "In particular, if ω is a 0-form, then dω = Dω.",
    "We denote byC ∞ c (R d, k R d) the set of smooth and compactly supported differential k-forms on R d. Recall that a linear functionalT: C ∞ c (R d, k R d) → R continuous in the sense of distributions is called a k-current.",
    "The linear space of all k-currents in R d is denoted by D k (R d).",
    "We say that T ∈ D k (R d) is of finite mass if it is represented as an integration against a k R d -valued measure.If T is of finite mass, then the induced measure is determined uniquely, its total variation measure, µ, is called the mass measure and we denoteµ(R d) = ∥T ∥."
  ]
